=====Behind the scenes=====
Rebecca Saire was only fourteen when the production was filmed, an unusually young age for an actress playing Juliet, although the character is just thirteen. In interviews with the press prior to broadcast, Saire was critical of director Alvin Rakoff, stating that in his interpretation, Juliet is too childlike and asexual. This horrified the series' producers, who cancelled several scheduled interviews with the actress in the lead-up to broadcast.<ref>Willis, p. 16.</ref>

The ''Prefaces to Shakespeare'' episode for ''Romeo & Juliet'' was presented by [[Peggy Ashcroft]], who had played Juliet in a 1932 [[Oxford University Dramatic Society]] production directed by John Gielgud. The ''Shakespeare in Perspective'' episode was presented by [[Feminism|feminist]] academic and journalist [[Germaine Greer]].

